data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
This application is for the PIC16F1454.
This application shows:
- Shows the USB connectivity status. This connectivity status uses events and timers to detect USB changes.
- You can set the state of the 16f1454 ports - use the LED check boxes to set the state of I/O 2, 3 and 4.
- You can read the I/O port status of the 16f1454. Select the 'Read' button to read the status of I/O ports 5, 6, 7 and 8.
- The application initialisation process the status of the LEDs is read and the state of LEDs is represented in the application
- Polls the microcontroller every 10 seconds after the last USB transmission. An LED attached to I/O 1 will toggle to show the polling operation.
- This application can recovery from USB physical D- and D+ errors by using a state engine.
- This application uses the LibK/WinUSB library.
Enjoy
